{"name":"Heralds of the Last Day","type":"deity","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>The Heralds of the Last Day includes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.deities.d56paSkcwvll2OhR]{Abadar}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.deities.KIEgpcmHYtFu1dpg]{Imot}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.deities.9EKyWmjLUu42evxC]{Nethys}, and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.deities.WloVxo6HXJdS4YTt]{Groetus}, along with other morally neutral deities with a vested interest in the end times. Depictions of this pantheon envision these deities as scholars poring over data tables and multifaceted equations. The Heralds’ sacred text is an ever-evolving collection of mathematical models known as The Soul Derivatives, which attempt to describe and predict population trends to extrapolate the date the last soul will depart from the Material Plane. Followers of this pantheon use their magical gifts to help population levels conform to their models, either through the preservation or elimination of life.</p>\n<p><strong>Edicts </strong>study world events and trends, provide measures of uncertainty to your claims </p>\n<p><strong>Anathema </strong>suppress knowledge relevant to the Last Day, drastically interfere in society’s unfolding or allow such drastic interference to go unchecked </p>"},"source":{"value":"Divine Causes and Inquisitions"},"rules":[],"slug":"heralds-of-the-last-day","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"category":"pantheon","alignment":{"own":"N","follower":["N","LN","CN"]},"domains":{"primary":["change","glyph","knowledge","time"],"alternate":["duty"]},"font":["harm","heal"],"ability":["int","wis"],"skill":"soc","weapons":["staff"],"spells":{"1":"Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.EUMjrJJwSgsqNidi","4":"Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.zvKWclOZ7A53DObE","6":"Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.OdqM06M0wDUqZWiR"}},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/deity.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686465735585,"modifiedTime":1686465953556,"